# {{.Type}}: {{.Name}}

{{ .Description | trimspace }}

API keys authenticate a service account against the Kosli API. Use this resource to mint and revoke keys for a service account managed with the `kosli_service_account` resource.

~> **Important:** The raw `key` value is returned **only once**, at creation time, and is stored in Terraform state as a sensitive value. It is SHA-256 hashed server-side and can never be retrieved again. Protect your Terraform state accordingly.

~> **Note:** API keys are immutable. Changing `description`, `expires_at`, or `service_account_name` revokes the existing key and creates a new one.

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/resources/kosli_service_account_api_key/resource.tf"}}

## Expiry

The `expires_at` attribute is a Unix timestamp (seconds). Omit it (or set it to `0`) for a key that never expires. The timestamp must not be in the past.

## Import

API keys can be imported using the `<service_account_name>/<key_id>` format:

{{codefile "shell" "examples/resources/kosli_service_account_api_key/import.sh"}}

Because the raw key value is only returned at creation time, the `key` attribute is empty after an import.

